post_text:
Tonight’s message to families:

Good Evening,

This is Maureen Binienda, Superintendent of the Worcester Public Schools.

Earlier today, Governor Baker announced that public schools will stay closed through the end of the school year. The last day of school for the WPS is June 12th. The Governor shared this is a necessary step to keep everyone as healthy as possible. I understand this announcement may result in a range of emotions among our staff, students and families. I want you to know the WPS staff will continue to help our students and their families through multiple ways such as phone calls, google chats, zoom calls and google voice. Remote learning is even more important now, and we will issue additional guidance to students and families later this week. The WPS District staff will be working during the next two weeks with high school principals and staff to address senior interests such as graduation, college acceptances, scholarships, and final grades. I will continue to keep you updated.
Thank you
text:
Tonight’s message to families:

Good Evening,

This is Maureen Binienda, Superintendent of the Worcester Public Schools.

Earlier today, Governor Baker announced that public schools will stay closed through the end of the school year. The last day of school for the WPS is June 12th. The Governor shared this is a necessary step to keep everyone as healthy as possible. I understand this announcement may result in a range of emotions among our staff, students and families. I want you to know the WPS staff will continue to help our students and their families through multiple ways such as phone calls, google chats, zoom calls and google voice. Remote learning is even more important now, and we will issue additional guidance to students and families later this week. The WPS District staff will be working during the next two weeks with high school principals and staff to address senior interests such as graduation, college acceptances, scholarships, and final grades. I will continue to keep you updated.
Thank you

post_text:
Good Evening,
>>>>>>> master

This is Maureen Binienda, Superintendent of Schools. As discussed in my Sunday morning message, schools will be open between the hours of 10am-6pm tomorrow for students to retrieve their personal belongings, medications and textbooks. Extended learning packets will also be available. Where possible, parents should accompany students to their school. Controlled student medications will only be given to parents.

Middle and high school students can retrieve their belongs without parents but will be expected to follow social distancing guidelines: no physical contact and a space of 6’ from others.

However, If you do not need to retrieve your belonging , textbooks or medications, please do NOT come to school to pick up learning packets. Packets will be mailed to your home.

Students and families are encouraged to also access the Worcester Public Schools website for regular updates.



Thank you

post_text: Community Reading Day at Clark Street!
shared_text:
Clark Street Community School - WPS
>>>>>>> master
March 4 at 1:44 PM ·

We’d like to thank the members of the Worcester Police Department (Official) and Worcester Fire Department that joined us at our school as part of the Community Readers Initiative. Our students enjoyed listening to our community members read, and hear from them of the importance of reading and writing in their professional lives. We had a great time focusing on reading here at Clark St Community School, and learning about the various roles Police Officers and Firefighters play in the community. Above all, we celebrated the reader in all of us during this Reading Across America Week.

#WPSLearns

Clark Street Community School - WPS
